<TITLE> Crescent Jute Mills fires another 336 workers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khulna, July 13 (bdnews24.com)  Authorities Friday retrenched another 336 workers of Crescent Jute Mills in Khalishpur industrial area of Khulna. The list of the sacked workers was hung on the gate of the mills at 4:00pm. A total of 981 workers of this Mill have been thrown out of job in three phases since June. Crescent Jute Mills Collective Bargaining Agents leader Mohammad Ali alleged the authorities took the decision at a meeting at the home of the chief of Crescent Jute Mill Sheikh Shamim Ahmed on Thursday. Ali said tension was brewing among the sacked workers. Earlier, 290 workers were sacked on June 4 and 5 and another 355 were retrenched on June 25 from the mills. bdnews2
